      "solution": "#include <stdio.h>\n\nint main(void) {\n    long long N;\n    scanf(\"%lld\", &N);\n\n    int steps = 0;\n\n    while (N >= 10) {\n        long long sum = 0;\n        while (N > 0) {\n            sum += N % 10;\n            N /= 10;\n        }\n        N = sum;\n        steps++;\n    }\n\n    printf(\"%lld\\n%d\\n\", N, steps);\n    return 0;\n}",
      "statement": "A number can be reduced by repeatedly summing its digits until only a single digit remains.\nThis process is called a digit‑sum reduction.\nThe final single‑digit result is known as the digital root.\nGiven a positive integer, perform digit‑sum reductions until a single digit remains and report:\n\nthe final digit\nthe number of reductions performed",
