    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">A number can be reduced by repeatedly summing its digits until only a single digit remains.<br>This process is called a digit‑sum reduction.<br>The final single‑digit result is known as the digital root.<br>Given a positive integer, perform digit‑sum reductions until a single digit remains and report:<br><br>the final digit<br>the number of reductions performed</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> A positive integer <var>N</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> The final single digit obtained after all digit‑sum reductions.<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> The number of reductions performed.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>N</var> &le; 10&sup1;⁵<br><br>All calculations fit within 64‑bit signed integers.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">9875</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">2\n3</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
